privacy policy
Budget Bestie Privacy Policy
Last updated:
February 26, 2025
Budget Bestie Corp ("Budget Bestie", "we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application (the "App"). It also outlines your rights concerning your personal data and how you can exercise them.
Please read this privacy policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this privacy policy, please do not access the App.
What data do we collect?
Budget Bestie collects the following data:
Personal identification information (Name, email address, phone number, etc.)
Financial information (e.g., income, expenses, savings goals)
Transaction data (e.g., purchase amounts, categories, dates)
Device information (e.g., iOS version, device model)
Usage data (e.g., how often the app is used, which features are accessed)
App performance data (e.g., crash reports)
Session replay data (e.g., screen recordings of app interactions, excluding sensitive information)
Advertising data (e.g., app install attribution, interactions with ads)
Device identifiers (e.g., IDFV - Identifier for Vendor) when you grant permission for advertising purposes
How do we collect your data?
You directly provide Budget Bestie with most of the data we collect. We collect data and process data when you:
Register for an account in our app
Manually enter your financial information and transactions
Use or interact with our app's features
Voluntarily complete a customer survey or provide feedback
Grant permissions to the app (such as push notifications or Face ID/Touch ID for login)
Budget Bestie may also collect some data automatically:
Device information is collected when you install and use our app
Usage data is collected as you interact with the app
App performance data, including crash reports, is collected to improve app stability
Session replay recordings are collected to understand how users interact with the app and identify usability issues
Advertising data is collected through our partner Branch to measure ad performance and app install attribution.
Device identifiers may be collected by TikTok when permission is granted for ad measurement and attribution
How will we use your data?
Budget Bestie collects and uses your data to:
Provide and maintain our budgeting service
Personalize and improve your experience within the app
Generate insights and reports about your financial habits and progress
Send notifications and updates related to your budget and financial goals
Respond to your questions and customer service requests
Analyze usage patterns to improve app functionality
Review session recordings to understand user behavior and improve app usability (sensitive information like passwords is automatically masked)
Prevent fraudulent activities and enhance security
Fix app crashes and improve app stability
Measure and analyze the effectiveness of advertising campaigns
Process and validate refund requests through our payment processor RevenueCat, which may include sharing usage data with Apple
Marketing Communications
We may use your personal data to send you marketing communications about our products and services. You will only receive marketing emails if you explicitly consent to them during the new user onboarding process in our app.
To stop receiving marketing emails, you can unsubscribe at any time by clicking the opt-out link provided in each email or by contacting us at
support@budgetbestie.app
.
When you consent to receiving marketing communications, we share your email address and other information (such as your name) with Customer.io, our email marketing service provider, to facilitate the delivery of these emails. Customer.io's use of your data is governed by their own privacy policy, which can be found at
Customer.io Privacy Policy
.
How do we store your data?
Budget Bestie securely stores your data using Firebase, a Google platform. Firebase ensures data security through:
Encryption in transit via HTTPS
Google Cloud's secure infrastructure
Built-in security rules to prevent unauthorized access
Data Retention and Deletion
We retain your personal data only as long as necessary to provide our services or comply with legal requirements.
Active Accounts:
Data is retained while your account is active.
Inactive Accounts:
If your account remains inactive for 24 months, we will notify you by email. If we receive no response within 30 days, your data will be deleted.
Data Deletion Requests:
You may request data deletion by contacting us at support@budgetbestie.app. Deletion requests will be completed within 30 days. Users can also delete their data by selecting the "Delete all data and account" option in the app's settings.
Third-Party Services and Data Sharing
We use third-party services to improve the app. These services collect some user data in compliance with their privacy policies:
PostHog: Product analytics and session replay
Crashlytics (Firebase): Crash reports
RevenueCat: Subscription management
Branch: Ad performance tracking and app install attribution
TikTok: Ad measurement and attribution through the TikTok SAN SDK
Customer.io: We use Customer.io to send marketing emails. They collect your email address and other information for the purpose of delivering these communications, based on your consent provided during onboarding.
International Data Transfers
Your data may be transferred to servers in the United States and other countries.
What are your data protection rights?
You have the right to access, rectify, delete, or restrict processing of your personal data. You may also object to data processing or request data portability.
Changes to Our Privacy Policy
We may update this policy periodically. Significant changes will be communicated through the app or via email.
Contact Us
If you have any questions, contact us at:
Email:
support@budgetbestie.appprivacy policy
